I have been to this establishment twice, and each time was awful. The place is extremely dilapidated, the service is awful, and the food is bad. Like others have mentioned is not very handicapped accessible; it's all stairs and a scary little ancient elevator.  The place is old. It seems it is not maintained well, or really not at all..There are cracks all over the walls, carpeting older than your grandparents, and dust in every corner.  THIS PLACE IS A  GAUDY, TACKY , CHEAP,  DISGUSTING, FILTHY ESTABLISHMENT WITH GARBAGE FOOD..  The decorations and ambiance are just tasteless, tacky, gaudy, and cheap. FAKE GOLD THROWN AROUND EVERYWHERE DOESN'T EQUAL CLASS when you can't even dust the place....Peggy Bundy has more taste than whoever decorated this place....The "Royalty feeling" they're aiming for is a joke. The place is over the top and plain freaking UGLY.  The staff were really unattentive, almost like wall decorations that moved every now and again. The food was mediocre at best, Wendy's chicken being more flavorful and juicy. Also, it's like the waitstaff cleared your plate about 10 minutes after serving you. It's like they know how bad and inedible the food is, they save you the time.  And the place wasn't heated at all. I was here twice in the winter, it wasn't warm out. It was like being in a freezer. This place can't even spring on cleaning let alone heat. I love dressing up to go out and feel sick after...I felt ill after both times I was here...but hey it could have also been the food that made me sick lol.  Was invited here a third time and passed. I'd rather stay home where it's cleaner, warmer, and the foods better....NEVER EVER coming back here or recommending it...in fact you couldn't pay me enough to return.

Someone else described this place perfectly " it is where good taste goes to die. "  This place is a train wreck. It's consistently bad. This place is an atrocious mess of gaudy decor, dirt, dust, based service, and awful food.  Ambiance - This place screams tacky. God awful fake gold splashed everywhere on top of years of layers of ancient dust and tacky fake murals...how is that classy? Whoever decorated this place has the taste of someone living in a low-budget mafia movie from the 80s. It doesn't seem like they clean or maintain it either. It's always freezing here and there are cracks all over the walls.  Food- I can't tell what's worse - the food or the actual establishment. The food is the driest I have ever had the unpleasant misfortune of trying. It's like trying to pass off cardboard as edible.  Staff- very unattentive. It's like they hate it as much as the patrons. They are also extremely unhelpful and clear your  plates before even asking if you're done...but the food is so terrible they're probably just saving you the time.  You couldn't pay me enough to come back here. This place is just as horrific as their atrocious commercials. Save yourself the time and money and go to McDonald's if you want something more appetizing.  They should really change their slogan to "We make your nightmares come true." Half hour at the coat check. Then again to buy drink tickets, and again to redeem them for drinks! Lots of people were upset about the poor organization. We lined up at 11:25pm for champagne and still ended up without drinks for toasting at midnight. It was incredible to witness so much incompetence. Never again!
